definition.value: A hydroxyaurone that is aurone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 6 and a methylenedioxy group across positions 4 and 5 respectively.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
Glutathione substituted on sulfor by a 2-hydroxyacyl group.
A catechin that is (-)-epicatechin in which the hydroxy group at position 4' is replaced by a methoxy group. It is a metabolite of (-)-epicatechin.
